	<div id="Content-Container" data-skip="Content"><div id="Content-Main"><div class="table-div"><div id="Content" class="table-cell">
		<section class="blog-article">
			<p>A sculpted, contoured face with defined cheekbones is a hallmark of facial attractiveness that many people desire. However, some individuals have naturally full or round cheeks due to prominent buccal fat pads, which can make the face appear wider and less defined. Buccal fat removal, also known as buccal fat pad excision, is a cosmetic procedure designed to slim the cheeks and enhance facial contours by removing a portion of the buccal fat pad. Dr. Manoj K Johar at <a href="https://www.theaesthetic.in/dr-manoj-k-johar-plastic-reconstructive-surgeon-noida-up/" title="Dr. Manoj K Johar">his practice</a> has extensive experience in <a href="https://www.theaesthetic.in/facial-implants/" title="Facial Implants">facial contouring procedures</a>, helping patients achieve the refined, chiseled look they desire.</p>

			<h2>What Is Buccal Fat Removal?</h2>
			<p>Buccal fat removal is a surgical procedure that eliminates a portion of the buccal fat pad, a naturally occurring mass of fat located in the hollow of the cheek between the facial muscles. The buccal fat pad contributes to the fullness and roundness of the lower cheeks, and its size is largely determined by genetics. While some people appreciate the youthful appearance that buccal fat provides, others find that overly prominent buccal fat pads create a chubby or puffy facial appearance that does not reflect their true body composition.</p>
			<p>During the procedure, the surgeon accesses the buccal fat pad through a small incision inside the mouth, carefully removes a portion of the fat pad, and closes the incision with absorbable sutures. The result is a slimmer, more contoured cheek that enhances cheekbone definition and creates a more angular, sculpted facial appearance. The procedure is permanent, as the removed fat cells do not regenerate.</p>

			<h2>Ideal Candidates for Buccal Fat Removal</h2>
			<p>Buccal fat removal is not suitable for everyone, and careful patient selection is essential to achieve optimal results. The ideal candidates for this procedure include:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Round or Full Faces:</strong> Individuals with persistently round or chubby cheeks despite maintaining a healthy weight are often excellent candidates.</li>
				<li><strong>Prominent Buccal Fat Pads:</strong> Patients whose buccal fat pads are disproportionately large relative to their facial structure.</li>
				<li><strong>Good Skin Elasticity:</strong> Younger patients with good skin elasticity tend to achieve the best results, as the skin will conform to the new facial contour.</li>
				<li><strong>Desire for Facial Contouring:</strong> Patients who want a more defined, angular appearance with enhanced cheekbone prominence.</li>
				<li><strong>Realistic Expectations:</strong> Understanding that the procedure provides subtle contouring rather than dramatic facial transformation.</li>
				<li><strong>Non-Smokers:</strong> Smoking impairs healing and increases the risk of complications, so non-smokers or those willing to quit temporarily are preferred.</li>
				<li><strong>Good General Health:</strong> Patients without significant medical conditions that could complicate surgery or recovery.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>It is important to note that buccal fat removal may not be appropriate for very thin individuals or those with naturally lean faces, as removing too much buccal fat can create a hollow, aged appearance. Dr. Johar carefully evaluates each patient's facial anatomy during the consultation to determine the appropriate amount of fat to remove.</p>

			<h2>The Buccal Fat Removal Procedure</h2>
			<p>Buccal fat removal is a relatively quick and straightforward procedure, typically completed within thirty to sixty minutes. It is performed on an outpatient basis under local anesthesia, allowing patients to return home the same day.</p>

			<h3>Preparation and Anesthesia</h3>
			<p>Before the procedure begins, Dr. Johar marks the incision sites inside the mouth and discusses the amount of buccal fat to be removed based on the patient's goals and facial anatomy. Local anesthesia is administered to the inner cheek area, numbing the treatment zone completely. The patient remains awake and comfortable throughout the procedure, and some may also receive mild sedation to enhance comfort.</p>

			<h3>Incision and Fat Removal</h3>
			<p>Through a small incision approximately two to three centimeters long, made on the inside of the cheek near the upper molars, Dr. Johar carefully dissects through the buccinator muscle to access the buccal fat pad. The fat pad is gently compressed, causing it to herniate through the incision, where a controlled portion is excised. The amount of fat removed is carefully measured to ensure symmetry and avoid over-correction. In most cases, a significant but conservative amount of fat is removed to achieve a noticeable yet natural-looking contour change.</p>

			<h3>Closing the Incision</h3>
			<p>After the desired amount of fat has been removed, the incision is closed with one or two absorbable sutures that dissolve on their own within one to two weeks. There are no external incisions or visible scars, and the entire procedure is completed through the inside of the mouth.</p>

			<h2>Recovery After Buccal Fat Removal</h2>
			<p>Recovery from buccal fat removal is generally quick and manageable. Here is a typical timeline:</p>

			<h3>Days 1-3: Initial Recovery</h3>
			<p>Mild swelling and soreness inside the mouth are common during the first few days. Patients should follow a soft or liquid diet to avoid irritating the incision sites. Applying cold compresses to the outside of the cheeks can help reduce swelling. Most patients can resume light activities within a day or two.</p>

			<h3>Days 4-7: Early Healing</h3>
			<p>Swelling continues to decrease, and patients can gradually transition back to a normal diet. The internal sutures begin to dissolve, and any discomfort typically subsides. Most patients feel comfortable returning to work and social activities within one week.</p>

			<h3>Weeks 2-4: Continued Improvement</h3>
			<p>By the second to fourth week, most swelling has resolved, and the new facial contour begins to become apparent. Patients can resume all normal activities, including exercise. The cheeks appear slimmer, and cheekbone definition is enhanced.</p>

			<h3>Months 1-3: Final Results</h3>
			<p>Complete healing from buccal fat removal typically takes one to three months. During this time, any residual swelling continues to subside, and the final results become fully visible. The cheeks appear sculpted and contoured, with enhanced cheekbone prominence that complements the overall facial structure.</p>

			<h2>Results and Benefits</h2>
			<p>Buccal fat removal provides several significant benefits for the right candidates:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Enhanced Cheekbone Definition:</strong> Removing buccal fat allows the natural bone structure of the cheeks to become more prominent.</li>
				<li><strong>Slimmer Facial Appearance:</strong> The procedure reduces cheek fullness, creating a more angular and contoured look.</li>
				<li><strong>Permanent Results:</strong> Once the buccal fat is removed, the results are permanent as the fat cells do not regenerate.</li>
				<li><strong>No Visible Scars:</strong> All incisions are made inside the mouth, leaving no external scars.</li>
				<li><strong>Minimal Downtime:</strong> Most patients return to normal activities within one to two weeks.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Potential Risks and Complications</h2>
			<p>Buccal fat removal is generally safe when performed by an experienced surgeon, but potential risks include infection, bleeding, asymmetry, nerve damage (which could affect facial sensation or movement), and over-removal of fat leading to a hollow or gaunt appearance. The buccal branch of the facial nerve runs near the surgical site, and while injury is rare, it is an important consideration. Dr. Johar discusses all risks during the consultation and takes meticulous care to avoid complications. Patients may also consider combining buccal fat removal with other procedures such as <a href="https://www.theaesthetic.in/facial-plasty-and-maxillofacial-surgery/" title="Facial Plasty">facial plasty</a> for comprehensive facial rejuvenation.</p>

			<h2>Combination with Other Procedures</h2>
			<p>Buccal fat removal can be effectively combined with other facial procedures to achieve comprehensive results. Common combinations include rhinoplasty, chin augmentation, facelift, and <a href="https://www.theaesthetic.in/facial-implants/" title="Facial Implants">facial implants</a>. Combining procedures can enhance overall facial harmony, reduce total recovery time, and provide more comprehensive results. During your consultation, Dr. Johar discusses whether combining buccal fat removal with other treatments would be beneficial for your specific goals.</p>

			<h2>Cost of Buccal Fat Removal in India</h2>
			<p>The cost of buccal fat removal in India typically ranges from INR 50,000 to 1,20,000, depending on the surgeon's experience, the facility, and whether additional procedures are performed simultaneously. The cost generally includes the surgeon's fee, anesthesia, facility charges, and post-operative follow-up visits. During your consultation, Dr. Johar provides transparent pricing and discusses all associated costs to help you make an informed decision.</p>

