			<div class="blog-faq"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Is buccal fat removal painful?</h3>
					<p>The procedure is performed under local anesthesia, so there is no pain during surgery. After the anesthesia wears off, patients may experience mild to moderate soreness for a few days, which is well-managed with prescribed pain medication. Most patients find the recovery quite comfortable.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long does buccal fat removal surgery take?</h3>
					<p>The procedure typically takes thirty to sixty minutes and is performed on an outpatient basis. Patients can return home the same day and resume light activities within one to two days.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>When will I see the results of buccal fat removal?</h3>
					<p>Initial results are visible within two to four weeks as swelling subsides. The final, contouring results are typically seen within one to three months after the procedure, once all residual swelling has resolved.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Are buccal fat removal results permanent?</h3>
					<p>Yes, the results are permanent. Once the buccal fat pad is removed, the fat cells do not regenerate. However, significant weight gain can affect overall facial fullness, though the treated area will remain slimmer than it would have been without the procedure.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Will buccal fat removal make me look older?</h3>
					<p>When performed conservatively by an experienced surgeon, buccal fat removal enhances cheekbone definition without creating a hollow or aged appearance. Dr. Johar carefully calibrates the amount of fat removed to achieve natural-looking results that complement your facial features.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can buccal fat removal be combined with other procedures?</h3>
					<p>Yes, buccal fat removal is commonly combined with rhinoplasty, chin augmentation, facelift, or facial implants for comprehensive facial contouring. Combining procedures can enhance overall results and reduce total recovery time.</p>
